<paragraph id="3D7B160BDE62FF97D6DCFE2BFE6A9C76" blockId="7.[174,1232,388,543]" pageId="7" pageNumber="210">
Diagnosis. 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE62FF97D7BFFE2BFDD79FF7" authority="Marusik &amp; Omelko, 2017" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2017" box="[384,573,388,414]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Nediphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lyleae" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE62FF97D7BFFE2BFDD79FF7" box="[384,573,388,414]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="210">Nediphya lyleae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="14837762DE62FF97D47AFE2BFD6F9FF6" box="[581,645,388,415]" pageId="7" pageNumber="210" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE62FF97D51BFE2AFC799FF7" authority="Marusik &amp; Omelko, 2017" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2017" box="[804,915,388,414]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Nediphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hippai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE62FF97D51BFE2AFC799FF7" box="[804,915,388,414]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="210">N. hippai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="14837762DE62FF97D5A4FE2BFC319FF6" box="[923,987,388,415]" pageId="7" pageNumber="210" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by carapace pattern and abdominal pattern with white guanine spots. It can be distinguished from the latter by the epigyne with median plate (
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE62FF97D49DFE6AFD209FB7" box="[674,714,453,478]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="210">Mp</emphasis>
) longer than wide 
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE62FF97D589FE6AFC279FB7" box="[950,973,453,478]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="210">vs</emphasis>
. wider than long (cf. 
<figureCitation id="A5FF0A8EDE62FF97D691FE4BFE689F96" box="[174,386,484,511]" captionStart="Figs 40–51" captionStartId="9.[174,213,1747,1769]" captionTargetBox="[189,1210,673,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-133@9.[189,1210,673,1697]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 40–51. Epigynes of Nediphya hippai sp. n. (40–41, 46, 49), N. padillai sp. n. (42), N. lehtineni (43, 50–51), N. lyleae sp. n. (44–45, 48) and Diphya macrophthalma (47). Scale = 0.2 mm. Abbreviations: Cd copulatory ducts, Er elongate anterior receptacles, Mp median plate, Re round proper receptacles, Rr round anterior receptacles." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454201" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454201/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="210">figs 43 and 44–45</figureCitation>
) and presence of femoral spines on legs I and II 
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE62FF97D5EDFE4AFC039F97" box="[978,1001,485,510]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="210">vs</emphasis>
. lacking on all legs in sibling species.
</paragraph>
<caption id="69BB4683DE62FF97D691F8ABFBA8995C" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454197" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6454197" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454197/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="210" startId="7.[174,213,1796,1818]" targetBox="[222,1182,565,1769]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph id="3D7B160BDE62FF97D691F8ABFBA8995C" blockId="7.[174,1232,1796,1845]" pageId="7" pageNumber="210">
Figs 26–33. Male palp of 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE62FF97D792F8ABFD8F9970" authority="Marusik &amp; Omelko, 2017" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2017" box="[429,613,1796,1817]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Nediphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lehtineni" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE62FF97D792F8ABFD8F9970" box="[429,613,1796,1817]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="210">Nediphya lehtineni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="14837762DE62FF97D451F8ABFD4E9973" box="[622,676,1796,1818]" pageId="7" pageNumber="210" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(26–31) and 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE62FF97D512F8ABFBFE9970" authorityName="Nicolet" authorityYear="1849" box="[813,1044,1796,1817]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Diphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrophthalma">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE62FF97D512F8ABFBFE9970" box="[813,1044,1796,1817]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="210">Diphya macrophthalma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(32–33): 26, 33 — retrolateral; 27 —ventral; 28 — dorsal; 29 —posterio-dorsal; 30, 32 — prolateral; 31 — anterior.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="69BB4683DE6DFF98D693F90AFCA2994C" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454199" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6454199" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454199/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="211" startId="8.[172,211,1701,1723]" targetBox="[189,1210,193,1652]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph id="3D7B160BDE6DFF98D693F90AFC5298BC" blockId="8.[172,1219,1701,1829]" pageId="8" pageNumber="211">
Figs 34–39. Male palp of 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE6DFF98D797F90AFDB598D3" authority="Marusik &amp; Omelko, 2017" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2017" box="[424,607,1701,1722]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Nediphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="8" pageNumber="211" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lehtineni" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE6DFF98D797F90AFDB598D3" box="[424,607,1701,1722]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="211">Nediphya lehtineni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="14837762DE6DFF98D458F90AFD7498D2" box="[615,670,1701,1723]" pageId="8" pageNumber="211" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
: 34–35 — whole palp, prolateral and retrolateral; 36 — anterio-ventral; 37 — anterio-dorsal; 38 — anterio-retrolateral; 39 — retrolateral.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D7B160BDE6DFF98D693F975FCA2994C" blockId="8.[172,1219,1701,1829]" pageId="8" pageNumber="211">
