<paragraph id="3D7B160BDE6FFF9AD6E4FED1FD0B9FD0" blockId="10.[166,1225,382,601]" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">
Epigyne as in 
<figureCitation id="A5FF0A8EDE6FFF9AD740FED1FDC89FF0" box="[383,546,382,409]" captionStart="Figs 40–51" captionStartId="9.[174,213,1747,1769]" captionTargetBox="[189,1210,673,1697]" captionTargetId="figure-133@9.[189,1210,673,1697]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Figs 40–51. Epigynes of Nediphya hippai sp. n. (40–41, 46, 49), N. padillai sp. n. (42), N. lehtineni (43, 50–51), N. lyleae sp. n. (44–45, 48) and Diphya macrophthalma (47). Scale = 0.2 mm. Abbreviations: Cd copulatory ducts, Er elongate anterior receptacles, Mp median plate, Re round proper receptacles, Rr round anterior receptacles." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6454201" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6454201/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">figs 44–45, 48</figureCitation>
; median plate longer than wider, copulatory ducts arched and separated by about one diameter at the base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D7B160BDE6FFF9AD6E4FE11FE5F9F90" blockId="10.[166,1225,382,601]" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. The new species is known only from the 
<typeStatus id="E27FA8A9DE6FFF9AD550FE11FC4B9FB0" box="[879,929,446,473]" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">type</typeStatus>
locality where 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE6FFF9AD270FE10FB239FB1" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2017" box="[1103,1225,446,472]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Nediphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="padillai">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE6FFF9AD270FE10FB239FB1" box="[1103,1225,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">N. padillai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also known to occur.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D7B160BDE6FFF9AD6E4FE51FEDF9C30" blockId="10.[166,1225,382,601]" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">
Etymology. The species name is a patronym in honour of our colleague Robin Lyle (Pretoria, 
<collectingCountry id="45D3569BDE6FFF9AD768FDB1FE1B9C50" box="[343,497,542,569]" name="South Africa" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">South Africa</collectingCountry>
), coauthor of the study of African 
<taxonomicName id="FAC46D88DE6FFF9AD5B5FDB1FC359C51" authorityName="Nicolet" authorityYear="1849" box="[906,991,542,568]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Diphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="10" pageNumber="213" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0FB0CA19DE6FFF9AD5B5FDB1FC359C51" box="[906,991,542,568]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="213">Diphya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Marusik &amp; Lyle in prepartion).
</paragraph>
